## 4. Careful words: what I can and can't claim

*Write what your work will be able to say (observed, directional, decision-support) — and what it never will (causal proof, 'predicting Google').*
#What I can claim: observed patterns and groupings in the data, directional trends ("this cluster tends to have low CTR"), and decision-support suggestions (use clusters to prioritize review).
#What I can't claim: causation (nothing here proves why), future predictions (clusters describe now, not what happens next), anything about Google's algorithm, "semantic" clustering (no article text, just metrics), or that a suggested action is guaranteed to work. Clusters are one useful lens, not ground truth.
